DO THIS BEFORE RUN THE PROGRAM

Before compile the program, you need to right click on the pacman.sh 
file then go to Permissions tab and change the following option:

Access -> Read & Write
Others -> Read & Write
Stick on Allow this file to run as a program

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FOR CREATE NEW MAP

When you type n filename.pac rows cols, after validate the row and col
then the map will be created. Next, you read that map and you will see the
border on the screen. Now you can draw a map inside the border. For example,

*************************
*//draw here            *
*                       *
*                       *
*************************

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FOR EDIT MAP

If you edit outside the row's length or col's length then all of that will be ignore
For example, the map with 3 rows and 5 cols, if you edit row number 4 or col number 6,
all of that will be ignore and will not be saved into the map.

